==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native image generation**\\n\\nI'm considering the first agent generation. The test involves using a native image that includes a test class. It seems that Class.forName might be supported if the application class is reachable. In this context, Class.forName should work with constants if the class is included. However, the string descriptions are dynamic. The agent will gather metadata during the JVM test without editing it. Okay, I need to finalize this and mention the fixed helper too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed `JUnitVersionHelperTest.readsIgnoreMessageFromJUnit4Facade()`.\n\nThe earlier version used `JUnit4TestAdapter#getTests()`, which can return a wrapper that does not satisfy `JUnitVersionHelper`’s exact `JUnit4TestCaseFacade` path, so `getIgnoreMessage(...)` returned `null`.\n\nUpdated:\n\n- `tests/src/org.apache.ant/ant-junit/1.10.15/src/test/java/org_apache_ant/ant_junit/JUnitVersionHelperTest.java`\n\nChange made:\n\n- Replaced `JUnit4TestAdapter#getTests()` with `JUnit4TestAdapterCache.getDefault().asTest(...)`\n- Created a `Description` for `ignoredTest`, which produces a real `JUnit4TestCaseFacade`\n- This keeps the test on the supported JUnit public API path and should now reach the intended `JUnitVersionHelper.getIgnoreMessage(...)` reflection call sites.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06d49b447e49bed7016a263aee9170819395b04982eb35d875\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 668, "output": 546, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33470, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780890341238, "responseId": "resp_06d49b447e49bed7016a263ae5c4e08193a59e6091b54a8951"}}
